Was tempted to sell the 165 or 170 at 40 DTE, but i've got too much on margin at the moment.

Gamma represents the rate of change between an option's delta and the underlying asset's price. After you pass the 21 DTE point gamma sharply increases and a small change in the underlying price can have a large effect on the options price. Holding after 21 days increases the risk of the position without significant (and proportional) increase in profit AKA: picking up pennies in front of a steam roller. 

&amp;#x200B;

I was halfway joking about selling naked ATM options. Only do this if you understand the risk of being in the naked position. It can absolutely go tits up fast.
